Text.val: -- All defined output parameters uses model 116 (N11C). although the output
parameters of BAD490 and BAD492 uses model 115 (N11.2C)
The VT06 amounts only supports model 116 and VT06 rows have to be only
written if the related amount of the output parameter <> 0
To avoid VT06_AMOUNT = 0 amounts, model 116 has to be used, because it'll be
possible that the output parameters returns
amounts (> - 1 and < 0) or ( > 0 and < 1), which is 0 in case of model 116
